description: Turkish police detained Lorenzo Prendini, a curator at the American Museum of Natural History, at Istanbul Airport after he allegedly attempted to smuggle about 1,500 spider and scorpion samples.
title: U.S. museum curator detained in Turkey for trying to smuggle dead spiders, scorpions

description: Thousands gathered outside parliament in Georgia’s capital Tbilisi to protest against a controversial “foreign agents” bill that has sparked a political crisis in the country. Two U.S. citizens were among those detained during overnight demonstrations aimed at blocking lawmakers from entering the building.
title: Thousands protest in Georgia against ‘foreign agents’ bill

description: The Biden administration has criticized Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu’s response in Gaza and the looming plans for a ground invasion in Rafah. NBC News’ Aaron Gilchrist reports on how Netanyahu is responding to the criticism and how this is straining the relationship between the two leaders.
title: Biden administration remains critical of Israel’s looming Rafah offensive

description: Palestinian families were seen leaving the urban Jabaliya refugee camp in northern Gaza after the area came under renewed intense Israeli bombardment. Many told an NBC News team that it was the latest in a series of displacements since Israeli troops invaded.
title: Palestinians flee Jabaliya in northern Gaza as Israel renews attack on the area

description: Six years after plunging Spain into its worst political crisis in decades, Catalonia’s separatist parties are in danger of losing their hold on power in the northeastern region after the pro-union Socialist Party scored a historic result in Sunday’s election.
title: Catalan separatists lose majority as Spain’s pro-union Socialists win regional elections

description: Two U.S. citizens and one Russian were among 20 people detained at protests in Tbilisi while Georgian lawmakers were debating a “foreign agents” bill that has sparked a political crisis, the interior ministry said on Monday.
title: Two Americans detained in Georgia as thousands protest ‘Russia-style’ law on foreign influence

description: Torrential rain triggered flash floods, landslides and cold lava flow, which is a mixture of volcanic ash, rock debris and water that flows like mud, in Indonesia's West Sumatra province.
title: Deadly Indonesian floods include cold lava flow from Mount Marapi

description: A small plane with three people aboard landed safely without landing gear in a "textbook wheels-up landing," after circling an Australian airport for almost three hours to burn off fuel, police said.
title: Watch: Small plane makes 'textbook wheels-up landing'

description: Amid warnings by the U.S. and others of a humanitarian catastrophe, Israeli forces have encircled Rafah in southern Gaza ahead of a ground operation. NBC News' Claudio Lavanga has the latest on Early Today.
title: 300,000 flee Rafah as Israeli forces encircle city
